    "verdict": "Re-banking wirbel #290's step-banked BUILT-raise target (4.9029, priced at the LINEAR drafter's step) against the HEAVIER EAGLE-3 multi-layer-fusion draft forward. The deployed linear draft is a SMALL 12.46% of the step (linear_draft = 149.84us < verify_step = 1052.88us; bridge-bounded by kanna #286 0.2147), so verify dominates. Modeling the EAGLE-3 draft as m_fuse x linear_draft (L_fuse=3 -> m_fuse~3-4): at the DEPLOYED m_fuse=3 the draft inflates 149.84 -> 449.52us (+299.68us step), raising the corrected target 4.9029 -> 6.1245 public E[T] (Delta +1.2217). That overhead (+1.2217) is 19.4x the #285 free-lever relaxation (0.0631) -> the heavier drafter EATS the free lever at EVERY m_fuse>=2 (corrected target > fern #281's un-banked 4.966 at all m_fuse>=2). The corrected target stays INSIDE the feasibility window at every swept m_fuse (max 7.9570 at m_fuse=6 < E_T_max 8.0; 99.0% of the cap->ceiling headroom eroded) -- the window HOLDS but the conservative m_fuse=6 bound nearly saturates it. Honest de-optimism: the step-overhead-corrected target the human-gated EAGLE-3 decision must size against is 6.1245 public E[T] (band [5.8017, 6.1245] over the denken #283 floor -> denken #278 bridge-bounded draft fractions), NOT 4.9029. The modeled draft-step remains BUILD-measured. BASELINE 481.53 untouched; analysis-only; NOT a launch.",
    "handoff": "pricing the EAGLE-3 drafter's heavier multi-layer-fusion draft forward (L_fuse=3, m_fuse=3) inflates the deployed linear draft-step from 149.84us to 449.52us, raising your #290 step-banked target from 4.9029 -> 6.1245 public E[T] (Delta +1.2217), which DOES eat your own #285 free-lever relaxation (0.0631) and KEEPS the target INSIDE the feasibility window (6.1245 < E_T_max 8.0) -- so the honest, step-overhead-corrected BUILT-raise target the human-gated EAGLE-3 decision must size against is 6.1245 public E[T] (band [5.8017, 6.1245]; the modeled draft-step remains build-measured)."
